Parameter.Name: TcpHeartbeatInterval
Parameter.Comment: BATS expects heartbeat messages to be sent to the GRP on live connections no less than every 5 seconds.

Parameter.Name: BatsmcAlwaysConnectToRetransLines
Parameter.Comment: This parameter overrides TcpConnectOnStartUp. When this parameter is true the feed handler will connect to the GRP lines during startup and remain connected while the feed handler is running. When this parameter is false the feed handler will only connect to the GRP lines when retrans is required, and then the feed handler will disconnect after the retrans is finished.

Parameter.Name: BatsmcProxyMaxQueuedRequests
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of the retrans requests staying in the queue. Once the queue is longer than this value (mostly because of too many retrans requests in a short time frame), the queue will be cleared for responding to the most lastest requests

Parameter.Name: BatsmcProxyMaxReconnectCount
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of reconnecting to GRP server. Every try will be delayed "TcpConnectDelay" millseconds.

Parameter.Name: BatsmcProxyRequestGapLimit
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of gap for each retrans request. Not like LineFilterGapLimit, any gap request over this number will be splitted to a group of requests.

Parameter.Name: BatsmcProxyExtraLogging
Parameter.Comment: Set to true to get more logging on GR Proxy line (useful during testing and debugging)

Parameter.Name: BatsmcProxyHeartbeatLogInterval
Parameter.Comment: Specifies the interval at which heartbeats will be logged. A value of 0 or less will disable heartbeat logging. BatsmcProxyExtraLogging must be true for this value to take effect.

DefineParameterGroup.Name: DirectEdgemcSpinParams
DefineParameterGroup.Comment: Common params used the spin lines.

Parameter.Name: BatsmcSpinMaxReconnectCount
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of reconnecting to Spin server. Every try will be delayed "TcpConnectDelay" millseconds.

Parameter.Name: BatsmcSpinHeartbeatLogInterval
Parameter.Comment: Specifies the interval at which heartbeats will be logged. A value of 0 or less will disable heartbeat logging. BatsmcSpinExtraLogging must be true for this value to take effect.
